                    <div class="article-content-area">
                      
                       <div id="pressRelease">
    <h3>2014 International CES Registration Now Open</h3>
    <h4></h4>
    <em>Arlington,&nbsp;VA&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;07/09/2013</em>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup> &reg; </sup>today opened registration for the 2014 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup>, the world&rsquo;s leading innovation event, scheduled to run January 7-10, 2014, in Las Vegas, Nevada. Attendees and media can register today at <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/">CESweb.org</a>.&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
New badges will be used for the 2014 CES that employ near field communication (NFC) technology and will result in shorter lines, more badge functionality and greater ease of use for attendees and exhibitors. For the 2014 CES, badges will not be mailed to registrants in advance. Instead, attendees are able to pick up badges at more than 25 designated locations in Las Vegas. Key pick up locations include McCarran International Airport baggage claim areas, <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/Hotel-Travel/Hotel-Reservations.aspx">official show hotels</a> and 2014 CES exhibit venues. These added locations will minimize lines and wait times on-site at the 2014 International CES.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
The International CES draws 150,000 of the top industry executives, retail buyers, content providers, entertainment executives, venture capitalists, engineers, government officials and media.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
&ldquo;This new badge process demonstrates another way that we are leveraging technology to make the CES experience better and more streamlined for CES attendees,&rdquo; said Karen Chupka, senior vice president, International CES and corporate business strategy, CEA. &ldquo;Reduced wait times for badges means that our attendees can spend more time networking, doing deals, seeing the future on the exhibit floor and attending our world-class conference sessions. With more than 3,200 exhibitors and every major tech company expected to participate, CES will bring decision makers from all of the major industries that touch technology together in one place to experience the latest in innovation.&rdquo;<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Attendees are encouraged to register in advance of the 2014 International CES to ensure minimal wait times on-site for their badge. Additional information on the 2014 CES, including hotel and airline information, can be found at <a href="http://cesweb.org/Hotel-Travel.aspx">CESweb.org</a>. CES has room blocks at discounted rates, available for a limited time, at partner hotels throughout Las Vegas.&nbsp; It is important to make hotel reservations early to secure the best rates.<br />
&nbsp;<br />
Note to Media: Registration for credentialed media is free. Please visit <a href="http://www.CESweb.org/register">www.CESweb.org/register</a>.<br />

    </div>
    <div class="pressAboutCEA">
        <strong>About CES</strong>
        <p>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is the preeminent trade association promoting growth in the $209 billion U.S. consumer electronics industry. More than 2,000 companies enjoy the benefits of CEA membership, including legislative advocacy, market research, technical training and education, industry promotion, standards development and the fostering of business and strategic relationships.&nbsp;CEA also owns and produces the International CES &ndash; The Global Stage for Innovation. All profits from CES are reinvested into CEA&rsquo;s industry services.&nbsp; Follow CES online at <a href="http://www.CESweb.org">www.CESweb.org</a> and through social media:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.cesweb.org/social" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="/CorporateSite/media/About-Media/new_social_icons.jpg" /></a> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
    </div>
    <div class="pressContact">
